Honestly I understand why Claire looked so irritated with Chris and Brad who were so excited and overzealous that they kept talking over her. And they were so happy with achieving honestly a lot less than what Claire has achieved in the past and would likely have achieved if she’d been doing this one (though it would probably have taken her 5 breakdowns and a whole weak) Claire’s perfectionism is her strength and weakness

But honestly the whole interaction was just hilarious. Not taking it seriously. Plus it was cool that they still recognized how they got a pretty easy on and that Claire’s frustrations with the show are usually on point
